docs.lead_paragraph: GUATEMALA, July 26 Representatives of the Central American Common Market and the Latin-American Free Trade Association have announced the establishment, in principle of a coordinating committee linking the two organizations. The two groups involve 16 Western Hemisphere nations.
docs.abstract: Central Amer Common Mkt and Latin-Amer Free Trade Assn reprs, after 2-day conf, Guatemala, agree in principle to establish coordinating com linking orgns; set foreign mins conf, Asuncion, Paraguay, for Sept

docs.snippet: In the Roman Catholic Church of SS. Gregorio and Siro in Bologna, Italy, yesterday afternoon, Marchesa Clementina Misciattelli, daughter of the Marchese and Marchesa Misciattelli delle Ripe of Bologna, became the bride of Richard Hynson Stollenwerck....
docs.lead_paragraph: In the Roman Catholic Church of SS. Gregorio and Siro in Bologna, Italy, yesterday afternoon, Marchesa Clementina Misciattelli, daughter of the Marchese and Marchesa Misciattelli delle Ripe of Bologna, became the bride of Richard Hynson Stollenwerck. His parents are Mr. and Mrs. Edward Carroll Stollenwerck of Greenwich, Conn.
